Christmas Day kisses 😘🎄

Today I am celebrating by putting on my snoopy Christmas pjs, with no extravagant plans and just focusing on the love and blessings I have. It is a special day regardless if you are spending it alone or with loved ones because it is still meaningful in its own way. 

I am truly grateful for what has already been blessed upon me. I genuinely believe everything happens for a reason and I know I have to put in the work, be better for myself so i can be better for the loved ones around me and give back to the community that nurtured and accepted me. 

This holiday season has been an interesting journey for me with new experiences and perspectives. Even though things may not always feel so jolly and magical.. it is ok. Everyone’s story is different, have faith everything will happen in gods time. 

Merry Christmas everyone 🎅🏻

I would love to know what everyone is up to on their Christmas Day celebrations. With family? friends? solo? Would love to hear it 🥰

Happy new year 🥳 

Everyone has been posting reels of their year, and I have really enjoyed them. But unfortunately I don’t take enough photos decent enough to be able to do the same (I will work on it … any tips? 😅)

My 2022 was very tough, even though there were many great moments this year… I would say this one was probably one of the toughest years i have had. But amongst all the pain and tears I have also learned and grown the most in 2022. It is still a process but behind the scenes of all my failures and successes, my development and the reason I am still standing tall is largely because of the support I have around me. 

As we say goodbye to 2022, I only feel  gratitude to the ones who have loved and supported me unconditionally. You guys push me in the right direction and lift me up when I’m at my lowest. Because of you guys I know things will always be ok .. so I would like to dedicate this new year post to just thank all my friends, family, sponsors, fans and supporters from near and far. I would not have survived 2022 without you guys and as exciting 2023 is, I am already feeling very blessed and grateful And very confident going into the new year knowing I have the support and team that I do. 

There are so many people I wish I have photos with that I could post here as well but like I said I need to start taking more and better photos! if your photo not here please know you are just as important to me and I’m very thankful for you ❤️

Special shout-out to my sponsors SK8 biotech, Yonex and BCOE you make what I do possible and your support and belief in me continues to drive me to reach new heights. 

Onwards to 2023 ☝🏽 and see you on court again soon ☺️

I had the honour of joining Solibad this trip to visit a little village in Bekasi. We played some badminton with the kids from the village then visited their homes. 
It was an incredible experience and we are truly blessed. 

Solibad and this little community built right on a garbage dump location has really come a long way. We even had to take motorbikes because there are no path for cars to go on. 

It was incredible to hear the stories and to witness their living conditions first hand. Having floor tiles and stone walls at home was a massive luxury. 

And to know what badminton means to them and how being apart of the solibad program has changed their lives … one girl who grew up here is en route to becoming a flight attendant and will be working in another 6 months. You have no idea how amazing and inspiring that is. 

And to all the kids we passed by in the village, didn’t matter how little they had, their spirit was so pure and still always greeted us with a smile. If you swipe to the second last slide, the video shows the magic that badminton brought to these kids. They probably had no idea who they were playing with, and the racquets we were using had no grip, a broken frame and broken string but the laughter and joy was so real. 

This trip really puts things into perspective and a little really goes a long way. Thank you Solibad for the opportunity and for opening my eyes to such inspiration and allowing me to witness what true mental toughness looks like. Hope we can continue to do more and hope to come back next time!

Week after week we put it all out there and recently my body and mind is saying I need a break. I tried but my hip and whole right side is giving out and restricting my movement on court. Unfortunately I will be pulling out of the upcoming tournament to take care of my body and reset. 

Past couple months have truly been a lot, too much even… but it has been good! One poor performance will not define or takeaway from the good and progress we have made. Everyone’s path is different and we will continue to make adjustments to find the way that works for us and will get us there. 

Looking forward to go home, recover and start again. This sport, this schedule, this pressure is extremely tough but when I think about about the people that continue to support me and the opportunity to do what I love, I know I’m blessed 🙏🏼 Staying patient, diligent and strong…  just a matter of time.

Long post warning ⚠️ 🤓

6 weeks on the road and last tournament was not the way I wanted to finish. I had my chances and I literally hit a wall. It surely doesn’t feel good, and it’s disappointing to say the least. So its hard enough to process my own feelings and criticism of what happened already but the amount of judgement and attacks from the outside can really confuse and make you want to doubt. 

I’m extremely grateful to have the unconditional supporters that would never feel the need to kick me when I’m down but continue to believe in me and lift me up when things don’t go well. Thank you 🙏🏼 

But one poor outcome at the tail end of a Long trip does not take away from the good that’s been done and the direction I’m going to keep moving in :) The labels and need people have to negatively attack can keep coming but will have no life here

I got so many valuable lessons and sparring this trip that i could only dream about in Canada. This trip alone I had over 10 matches with the best players in the world, to me that makes this trip extremely positive. 

I fought with all I got every single week and one slip in performance, will not rob me of the good and the lessons. No one likes to lose and I wouldn’t ever want to feel the way I did yesterday again but I’m human and I’m not perfect. There’s no doubt I’m going to keep putting in the work and probably may fall again but I know it’s all part of the plan and I’m not going to quit. 

@ryanmcvety @brendanwitton I watched D.I.R.T. The sequel yesterday when I was at my lowest (not really knowing what it was about) and wow. The timing and the word was perfect, so. powerful. Thank you 🙏🏼 

Shoutout to @chao_yu_kan for being on this journey with me and supporting me with what I need. I know it can be just as hard on coaches sometimes. Thank you @chimaican1 @petrovskristaps for being here as well. Truly is a team effort. 

Looking forward to going home and getting some needed rest then starting it back up again. Thank you everyone for the support 🙏🏼 
Still a long year ahead, everything happens for a reason and our time will come 💪🏽

Having the support of the crowd is an incredible feeling, and I'm disappointed I couldn't maximize the opportunity here at home this year. It was a good game my opponent played, where I was slow to start, and she never gave it to me easy. I really had to work and fight my way back in the second. The slip in the end was rough timing, and sustaining an injury here at the canada Open was not part of the plan. That's the worst of it all but I know with the right recovery I'll be ok. 

Recently, everything has been a bit of a struggle, and changes are happening constantly. Sometimes things happen, and we need to take a couple of steps back... re-assess, and start fresh to go further in the future. Having a clear mind and maintaining that positive energy to keep pushing forward is so important. But. you never stop working. So I'll keep my head down and keep putting in the work.There's no quitting here and im super grateful for the support i do have around me that continue to lift me up and not give up on me especially when things are hard. This was not how i hoped my run here at the Canada Open would go. But for me, some time right now is what I need to be back stronger.

It's actually amazing to have this caliber tournament here in Canada, and I want to thank all the Canadians, friends and fans for cheering me and other canadians on here. Special shout out to the organizers, sponsors, volunteers and bcan for putting together this level tournament 👍 it's incredible for the sport and for the players from this side of the world to experience and I hope this is just the beginning for more in the future.

Some just see outcome, some just see numbers, but many don’t see the process and today was really all about that. 

I can’t really put into words what this process has been like but 4 months post surgery, and literally having to rebuild everything from scratch, I got to be on court and feel the rush of competition again 🥹 It may not have been a pretty game today but just being on court today and having my leg strong enough to finish the game was an absolute blessing and a product of months and months and MONTHS of hard work NOT just by me, but by those around me who dedicated their time and efforts to get me to where I need to be 🙏🏼 

I am truly grateful to those who worked so diligently with me to get me here and to progress the way we have in this short amount of time is such a gift and reflection of how much more we can accomplish. (Maybe I’ll post more of what the process looked like soon 😅)

I’ve felt so much change and growth in this process and I just want to say thank you for the unconditional support from everyone near and far that understands what I’ve been going through, the love and kind gestures and words of positivity from friends, fans, and sponsors, during my not so good times is extremely encouraging and really helps to keep me moving forward. 

Recovery can’t be rushed and even though we’re still in the rehab process I am excited to keep digging, trusting the process and in time we will shine again 🌟☺️🙏🏼 

Thank you Malaysia for my first tournament back. I’m very happy to be here :) and happy new year everyone.
